   "source": [
    "# Reinforcement Learning for Dynamic Test Flow Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "## Post-Silicon Validation Optimization Using RL\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a comprehensive introduction to **Reinforcement Learning (RL)** fundamentals and demonstrates how to apply RL to optimize test flow selection in semiconductor post-silicon validation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What You'll Learn\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **RL Fundamentals**: Agent, Environment, State, Action, Reward, Policy\n",
    "2. **Q-Learning**: Classic RL algorithm with tabular approach\n",
    "3. **Deep Q-Networks (DQN)**: Neural network-based RL\n",
    "4. **Practical Application**: Dynamic test flow selection for semiconductor testing\n",
    "5. **Performance Comparison**: Random vs RL-based test selection\n",
    "\n",
    "### Problem Statement\n",
    "\n",
    "In post-silicon validation, we need to select the optimal sequence of tests to:\n",
    "- **Maximize defect detection** (find failing chips quickly)\n",
    "- **Minimize testing cost** (reduce time and resources)\n",
    "- **Adapt dynamically** (learn from test results)\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a perfect problem for Reinforcement Learning!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1: Setup and Data Loading\n",
    "\n",
    "First, we'll import necessary libraries and load our synthetic post-silicon test data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import libraries\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "from collections import defaultdict, deque\n",
    "import random\n",
    "\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set random seeds for reproducibility\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style for visualizations\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"pastel\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Libraries imported successfully\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ NumPy version: {np.__version__}\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Pandas version: {pd.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
