   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2: Reinforcement Learning Fundamentals\n",
    "\n",
    "Before diving into the implementation, let's understand the core concepts of Reinforcement Learning.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Concepts\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reinforcement Learning** is a type of machine learning where an agent learns to make decisions by interacting with an environment. The agent receives rewards or penalties based on its actions and learns to maximize cumulative rewards over time.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Agent\n",
    "The decision-maker (in our case, the test selection system)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Environment\n",
    "The world the agent interacts with (the semiconductor testing system)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. State (s)\n",
    "The current situation of the environment (which tests have been performed, current results)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Action (a)\n",
    "A choice the agent can make (select which test to perform next)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Reward (r)\n",
    "Feedback from the environment (positive for detecting defects efficiently, negative for wasting resources)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 6. Policy (π)\n",
    "The agent's strategy for selecting actions (how to choose the next test)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 7. Value Function (V or Q)\n",
    "Expected cumulative reward from a state or state-action pair\n",
    "\n",
    "### The RL Loop\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "1. Agent observes State (s)\n",
    "2. Agent takes Action (a) based on Policy (π)\n",
    "3. Environment transitions to new State (s')\n",
    "4. Environment gives Reward (r)\n",
    "5. Agent updates Policy to maximize future Rewards\n",
    "6. Repeat\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: Building the Test Environment\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll create a custom environment that simulates the semiconductor testing process. This environment follows the standard RL interface with `reset()` and `step()` methods."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class TestFlowEnvironment:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Semiconductor Test Flow Environment for Reinforcement Learning\n",
    "    \n",
    "    State: Binary vector indicating which tests have been performed\n",
    "    Action: Integer representing which test to perform next (0-9)\n",
    "    Reward: Based on defect detection efficiency and cost\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, chip_data, test_config):\n",
    "        self.chip_data = chip_data\n",
    "        self.test_config = test_config\n",
    "        self.test_names = list(test_config.keys())\n",
    "        self.num_tests = len(self.test_names)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Current state variables\n",
    "        self.current_chip = None\n",
    "        self.tests_performed = None\n",
    "        self.total_cost = 0\n",
    "        self.total_time = 0\n",
    "        self.defect_detected = False\n",
    "        self.done = False\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def reset(self):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Reset environment with a new random chip\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Select a random chip\n",
    "        self.current_chip = self.chip_data.iloc[np.random.randint(len(self.chip_data))]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Reset state\n",
    "        self.tests_performed = np.zeros(self.num_tests, dtype=int)\n",
    "        self.total_cost = 0\n",
    "        self.total_time = 0\n",
    "        self.defect_detected = False\n",
    "        self.done = False\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return self.tests_performed.copy()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def step(self, action):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Perform a test (action) and return next state, reward, done flag\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            action: Index of test to perform (0 to num_tests-1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            next_state: Updated state after performing test\n",
    "            reward: Reward for this action\n",
    "            done: Whether episode is complete\n",
    "            info: Additional information\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        if self.done:\n",
    "            raise ValueError(\"Episode is done. Call reset() to start new episode.\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Check if test already performed\n",
    "        if self.tests_performed[action] == 1:\n",
    "            # Penalty for repeating a test\n",
    "            return self.tests_performed.copy(), -10, False, {'reason': 'repeated_test'}\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Perform the test\n",
    "        test_name = self.test_names[action]\n",
    "        test_info = self.test_config[test_name]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Update state\n",
    "        self.tests_performed[action] = 1\n",
    "        self.total_cost += test_info['cost']\n",
    "        self.total_time += test_info['time']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get test result (pass=1, fail=0)\n",
    "        test_result = self.current_chip[test_name]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Calculate reward\n",
    "        reward = 0\n",
    "        info = {}\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if test_result == 0:  # Test failed - defect detected!\n",
    "            self.defect_detected = True\n",
    "            self.done = True\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Reward based on efficiency:\n",
    "            # - High reward for detecting defect early (fewer tests)\n",
    "            # - Lower reward if many tests were needed\n",
    "            num_tests_used = np.sum(self.tests_performed)\n",
    "            efficiency_bonus = (self.num_tests - num_tests_used + 1) * 5\n",
    "            cost_penalty = -self.total_cost * 0.5\n",
    "            \n",
    "            reward = 50 + efficiency_bonus + cost_penalty\n",
    "            info = {\n",
    "                'reason': 'defect_detected',\n",
    "                'num_tests': num_tests_used,\n",
    "                'efficiency_bonus': efficiency_bonus,\n",
    "                'cost_penalty': cost_penalty\n",
    "            }\n",
    "            \n",
    "        else:  # Test passed\n",
    "            # Small penalty for cost\n",
    "            reward = -test_info['cost'] * 0.5\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check if all tests are done\n",
    "            if np.sum(self.tests_performed) == self.num_tests:\n",
    "                self.done = True\n",
    "                # Check if chip actually has defect (missed detection)\n",
    "                if self.current_chip['defect_type'] != 'no_defect':\n",
    "                    # Large penalty for missing defect\n",
    "                    reward = -100\n",
    "                    info = {'reason': 'missed_defect'}\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    # Small reward for correctly identifying good chip\n",
    "                    reward = 10\n",
    "                    info = {'reason': 'good_chip_verified'}\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                info = {'reason': 'test_passed'}\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return self.tests_performed.copy(), reward, self.done, info\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def get_available_actions(self):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return list of tests that haven't been performed yet\"\"\"\n",
    "        return [i for i in range(self.num_tests) if self.tests_performed[i] == 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ TestFlowEnvironment class defined\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nEnvironment Interface:\")\n",
    "print(\"  - reset(): Start new episode with random chip\")\n",
    "print(\"  - step(action): Perform test and get reward\")\n",
    "print(\"  - get_available_actions(): Get list of available tests\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test the environment\n",
    "print(\"Testing the environment...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "env = TestFlowEnvironment(df_chips, test_config)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reset and get initial state\n",
    "state = env.reset()\n",
    "print(f\"Initial State: {state}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Current Chip Defect: {env.current_chip['defect_type']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Available Actions: {env.get_available_actions()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take a few random actions\n",
    "print(\"\\nTaking random actions:\")\n",
    "for i in range(3):\n",
    "    available_actions = env.get_available_actions()\n",
    "    if not available_actions or env.done:\n",
    "        break\n",
    "    \n",
    "    action = np.random.choice(available_actions)\n",
    "    test_name = env.test_names[action]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    next_state, reward, done, info = env.step(action)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\nStep {i+1}:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Action: {action} ({test_name})\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Reward: {reward:.2f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Done: {done}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Info: {info}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if done:\n",
    "        print(f\"\\nEpisode finished!\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Total Cost: ${env.total_cost}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Total Time: {env.total_time} minutes\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Tests Used: {np.sum(env.tests_performed)}/{env.num_tests}\")\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✓ Environment test complete!\")"
   ]
  }
