    "## Part 6: Key Insights and Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### What Did the Agent Learn?\n",
    "\n",
    "The Q-Learning agent learned to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Prioritize high-coverage tests**: Tests with better defect detection rates are selected first\n",
    "2. **Balance cost and effectiveness**: Expensive tests are used only when necessary\n",
    "3. **Detect defects early**: Minimize the number of tests needed to find failures\n",
    "4. **Avoid redundant testing**: Skip unnecessary tests once defect is detected\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why RL Works Better Than Random\n",
    "\n",
    "**Random Policy**: No learning, treats all tests equally, wastes resources on ineffective tests\n",
    "\n",
    "**Q-Learning Policy**: Learns from experience which tests are most effective for different scenarios, optimizes test sequence based on cumulative knowledge\n",
    "\n",
    "### Real-World Impact\n",
    "\n",
    "In semiconductor manufacturing:\n",
    "- **Reduced testing time**: Faster time-to-market\n",
    "- **Lower costs**: Fewer unnecessary tests\n",
    "- **Better quality**: Higher defect detection rates\n",
    "- **Scalability**: Adapts to new test types and chip designs"
